Final arguments are set to begin in the Air India bombing trial involving Sikh extremists in Canada.
Two suitcase bombs were checked onto Vancouver flights, leading to the deadliest terrorist act until 9/11.
The accused, Malik and Bagri, are charged with murder and conspiracy.
Witnesses, including women close to the suspects, play a crucial role.
The trial, overseen by Justice Josephson, has spanned 19 months.
Prosecutors argue the bombs originated in Vancouver, seeking justice for the 329 lives lost.
Despite challenges, the case hinges on confessions and motives of the accused, highlighting the complex nature of the trial.
